ZH: 他在挫折面前一蹶不振。
EN: He was unable to recover from the setback.

ZH: 她遇到困难后一蹶不振。
EN: She faltered after facing difficulties.

ZH: 我们不能因为失败而一蹶不振。
EN: We can't give up because of failure.

ZH: 面对艰难，我们不能一蹶不振。
EN: In the face of difficulties, we cannot falter.

ZH: 尽管遇到困难，他从不一蹶不振。
EN: Despite facing difficulties, he never falters.

